args: Commander Balboa's quarters,\nafter the attack on the base begins...
Allow me to formally welcome you to my\nbase, Commander. I trust you'll enjoy your\nstay. Tea? Or perhaps you're a coffee gal?
I'll pass, thanks. Instead, let's discuss why\nI'm here; I'm unaware of anything I've\ndone to earn such a forceful invitation.
I do apologize—though you must admit\nyou've resisted my prior overtures.
Yes, I've been rather busy of late.\nApologies if I gave the wrong impression.
Perish the thought. I merely hoped to get\nto know you better—as two commanders\nof the Svenitlan forces, you understand.
This seems a perfect opportunity for us\nto indulge in a bit of small talk, yes?
Are you aware that some within our great\nnation are toiling to dethrone the king?\nImagine the sheer audacity of it!
I've heard vague rumors, though I tend not\nto put much stock in them.
If I thought you truly believed that, I'd have\ncause to reevaluate my opinion of you.\nBut I think we both know better.
I expect you are quite familiar with\nthe movement I refer to.
I won't bore you with questions. All I wish\nto know is whether you're with him or not.
And who, pray, might this mysterious\n＂him＂ be?
We're both busy people, Commander—\ntoo busy to waste time on cheap farce.\nAnswer my question.
You've taken the words out of my mouth,\nCommander: I haven't the time for this.
I demand to know on what grounds I am\nbeing subjected to this interrogation.

You and I are equal in rank, and I had
intended to offer you every professional
courtesy—but always remember that I
do not answer to you.
Also, if you refuse to extend the same\ncourtesy to me, I'm quite happy to answer\nin kind. Is that how you want this to go?
You fail to understand your current\nposition, Commander.
You've failed twice now. First regarding\nthe alliance with Dyrenell, and now with\nthe procurement of new weaponry.
I'm beginning to question your\ncapabilities as a commander—\nand I'm not the only one.
You're likely one mistake short of being\nasked to resign. A mistake like, say, if the\nenemy were to lay claim to your base?
Yes, I hear roving bands of armed bandits\nare on the prowl of late. I pray they don't\ncause you any trouble.
Are you threatening me now, you dog?!
You're welcome to take it however you\nwish. Now let me repeat my query:
Just where does your allegiance lie,\nCommander Kirsty? Is it with your king...\nor perhaps somewhere else?
You know damn well I serve no master\nbut Svenitla herself.
And this conversation has convinced me\nthat I will crush every last locust gnawing\nat her body with my own two hands.
It's a real shame, Commander, to see\nthat you're not attached to your position\nOR the lives of your men.
Neither they nor I are so weak as to fall\nfor your sad, two-bit schemes.
Oh? Then I shall look forward to the show.\nIt will be quite the delight to see how long\nyour precious men last... Heh heh heh.

...We're completely outnumbered. Not only
that, but the enemy—they may be dressed
like common bandits, but it sounds like
they're actually the army in disguise.
Thanks, Noelle. Given the timing with what\nhappened to Kirsty, it's probably safe to\nassume these are Balboa's lackeys.
So, how hosed are we, Aggie?\nHow are supplies looking?

If we're just eating and sleeping, we've got
enough to last a month. But if we're, you
know, actually FIGHTING, our weapons
aren't going to last.
Not surprised to hear it. So if a protracted\nsiege is out, we'll need to settle things\nin one quick, decisive battle.
Bring it on! We'll show these curs\nhow Kirsty's soldiers fight!
Grab your weapons, boys and girls!\nDefensive formation, just like in training!

Everyone slow down! These men are
working for Balboa, which means they
may be well-informed on our army's
standard tactics.
You have a different plan, then?
I'm thinking we give 'em the old fake-out,\nand here's how...
The commander's too good to us; I can't\nbelieve we're all gonna get promotions\njust for mopping up a few traitors!
Sure, IF we live. These are well-trained\nsolders we're going after here, which is\nwhy we all have orders to kill on sight.
So look sharp! The commander says they'll\ngather their forces at one point and launch\na defensive—
Looks like they're biting. Aggie! Marsh!\nYou know what to do!
Sir, they're flooding out of the base from\nevery which way! They even seem to be\nsprouting from the GROUND!

Hidden tunnels, is it? Well, this is their
turf, so they were always going to have the
terrain advantage! We'll just have to use
our numbers to overpower them!
Concentrated mana, sir! It's from an\nextremely long range, but it's coming in\nfaster than anything I've ever seen!
Impossible. The brief said there were\nnext to no mages stationed here!
Well, looks like that's got 'em shook.\nThe fact they know all about us means\nthey're even less prepared for magic.
They weren't kidding when they said\nmanacasters were big news... You're a\none-man diversion, Joachim.
At the very least, you made 'em think twice\nabout coming any closer.
Hey, it's all the manacaster, not me.\nSave the kudos for Chanzelia and Kirsty.
Aw, don't be so modest! I knew we'd be\nfine with you calling the shots.
Er, is that weird? I mean, you ARE Kirsty's\nright-hand man, after all. Why wouldn't\nyou take command with her out?
Because you and me are practically the\nsame rank, Aggie!
Only 'cause you turn down promotions like\nthey're going out of style! But we all still\nknow you've got what it takes to lead.
Yeah, you're the most decisive one here,\nso let's keep the pressure on these guys.\nAwaiting orders, Mr. Acting Commander!
(Oh man, Joachim seems a little...\nWell, I just hope he's okay.)
